import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
    
def cope_payornot(varargin = None): 
    # cope_payornot - Does consistency and task performance quality checks for
# data gathered for the COPE study. This is meant to analyze data from
# participants who have completed the full main module--Survey2 and Tasks.
    
    # OUT:
# summary - structure with performance data on each of the tasks and
# phenomonology
    
    ## Get file containing data.
    if len(varargin) == 1:
        cell = varargin[1,1]
    else:
        if len(varargin) == 0:
            file,path = uigetfile('*')
            __,__,cell = xlsread(fullfile(path,file))
    
    ## Config.
    plot_yesno = 1
    
    ## Identify exclusions.
    
    # Exclude if have already been reviewed or included.
    
    task_already_reviewed = cell2mat(cell(np.arange(2,end()+1),(find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'task_quality_check',0,1))))
    task_already_included = cell2mat(cell(np.arange(2,end()+1),(find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'task_quality_check2',0,1))))
    consistency_already_reviewed = cell2mat(cell(np.arange(2,end()+1),(find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'consistency_quality_check',0,1))))
    consistency_already_included = cell2mat(cell(np.arange(2,end()+1),(find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'consistency_quality_check2',0,1))))
    incomplete_visual = cellfun(isnumeric,cell(np.arange(2,end()+1),find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'task_data_visual',0,0)))

    cell_in = cell_in(not false_completes_in ,:)

            plt.figure('Color',np.array([1,1,1]))

    else:
        if len(varargin) == 0:
            file,path = uigetfile('*')
            __,__,cell = xlsread(fullfile(path,file))

    plot_yesno = 1

    # redo_data = cell_in(2:end,(find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'task_data',1) & ~find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'complete',1) & ~find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'qualifying',1) ...

#     & ~find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'fu',1) & ~find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'short_t',1) & ~find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'2ifc',1) ...
#     & (find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'auditory',1) | find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'visual',1) | find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'yanny',1) ...
#     | (find_in_cellstr(cell_in(1,:),'dots',1)))));
    
    complete_redo_tasks = redos(1,np.sum(cellfun(isstr,redo_data), 1-1) > 0)
    complete_redo_task_data = redo_data(np.sum(cellfun(isstr,redo_data), 2-1) > 0,np.sum(cellfun(isstr,redo_data), 1-1) > 0)
    # Get rid of aberrant content (error in filling data w/ font color html.
    for i in np.arange(1,task_data.shape[1-1]+1).reshape(-1):

            if str(task_data[i,ii]) == str('<font color="red">Incomplete</font>'):

            else:
                if np.isnan(task_data[i,ii]):
                    task_data[i,ii] = NaN
                else:
                    if len(task_data[i,ii])==0:
                        task_data[i,ii] = NaN
    
    subs_w_full_data = np.sum(cellfun(isstr,task_data), 2-1) == main_tasks.shape[2-1]
    tasks = np.array([main_tasks,complete_redo_tasks])
    record_id_full_data = record_id(subs_w_full_data,1)
    task_data_full_data = task_data(subs_w_full_data,:)
    ## Run analysis on subjects with full data.
    task_output = redcap_reformat(task_data_full_data)
    ## Run analysis on subjects who have had to re-do tasks.
    redo_output = redcap_reformat(redo_data)
    ## Combine regular output with redo output for any tasks needing to be reported.
    
    if (task_output.shape == redo_output.shape):
        output = np.array([task_output,redo_output])
    else:
        output = np.array([task_output])
        output_redo = np.array([redo_output])
    
    ## Create an array of quality measures (and whether they meet certain benchmarks) for each task.
    
    # Names of measures:
# 1) first_15:  percentage of "yes" responses on first 15 trials of
# train_test.
# 2) delta_blocks: decreasing rate of "yes" response over blocks.
# 3) delta_cond: decreasing rate of "yes" response over conditions (75#-0#)
# 4) randomness: statistical randomness of sequence of responses.
    
    test_names = np.array(['Percent "Yes" First 15 Trials','Change in "Yes" Over Conditions'])
    empties = np.zeros((task_data_full_data.shape[1-1],tasks.shape[2-1]))
    for sub in np.arange(1,task_data_full_data.shape[1-1]+1).reshape(-1):
        # First cell is the name of the participant
        results.raw[sub,1] = record_id_full_data(sub,1)
        results.flags[sub,1] = record_id_full_data(sub,1)
        for task in np.arange(1,tasks.shape[2-1]+1).reshape(-1):
            if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_visual',0,1):
                task_type = 'vch'
                col = 1
            else:

                    task_type = 'ach'
                    col = 1
                else:
                    if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_yanny_laurel_control',0,1):
                        task_type = 'ylct'
                        col = 1
                    else:
                        if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_dots_control',0,1):
                            task_type = 'dct'
                            col = 1
                        else:
                            if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_visual_redo',0,1):

                                col = 2
                            else:
                                if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_auditory_redo',0,1):
                                    task_type = 'ach'
                                    col = 2
                                else:
                                    if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_yanny_laurel_control_redo',0,1):
                                        task_type = 'ylct'
                                        col = 2
                                    else:
                                        if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_dots_control_redo',0,1):
                                            task_type = 'dct'
                                            col = 2
                                        else:
                                            if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_auditory_short_b',0,1):
                                                task_type = 'ach'
                                                col = 2
                                            else:
                                                if find_in_cellstr(tasks(1,task),'task_data_auditory_short_t',0,1):
                                                    task_type = 'ach'
                                                    col = 2
                                                else:
                                                    task_type = ''
            if str(task_type) == str('ach') or str(task_type) == str('vch'):
                if isfield(output[sub,col],task_type):
                    # Go through the tests.
                    response_data = eval(np.array(['output{sub,col}.',task_type,'{1,1}.summary.detection.all;']))
                    percent_data = eval(np.array(['output{sub,col}.',task_type,'{1,1}.summary.detection.percent_responses']))
                    block_mod = fitlm((np.arange(1,(percent_data.shape[2-1] - 2)+1)),percent_data(6,np.arange(1,end() - 2+1)))
                    cond_mod = fitlm((np.arange(25,75+25,25)),percent_data(np.arange(2,4+1),end()))
                    rand_h,rand_p,rand_stats = runstest(response_data)
                    results.raw[sub,task + 1][1,1] = mean(response_data(np.arange(1,15+1),1))
                    #results.raw{sub,task+1}(1,2) = table2array(block_mod.Coefficients(2,1));  # Fit coefficient. Should be negative.
#results.raw{sub,task+1}(2,2) = table2array(block_mod.Coefficients(2,4));  # Fit P value.  In case this works better.
                    results.raw[sub,task + 1][1,2] = table2array(cond_mod.Coefficients(2,1))
                    results.raw[sub,task + 1][2,2] = table2array(cond_mod.Coefficients(2,4))
                    #                 results.raw{sub,task+1}(1,4) = rand_p;                       # P value for randomness test.
                    results.flags[sub,task + 1][1,1] = results.raw[sub,task + 1](1,1) >= 0.55
                    #results.flags{sub,task+1}(1,2) = results.raw{sub,task+1}(1,2)<0; # If there's a negative slope over the course of the experiment.
                    results.flags[sub,task + 1][1,2] = results.raw[sub,task + 1](1,2) > 0
                    #                 results.flags{sub,task+1}(1,4) = rand_p<0.05;
                    results.tasks = tasks
                else:
                    results.flags[sub,task + 1] = NaN
                    empties[sub,task] = NaN
            else:
                if str(task_type) == str('ylct') or str(task_type) == str('dct'):
                    #  Assuming actual reaction times should be higher than minimum
#  reaction time to auditory detection (200ms):
#  Green, David M., and R. Duncan Luce. "Detection of auditory signals
#  presented at random times: III." Perception & Psychophysics
#  9.3 (1971): 257-268.
                    if isfield(output[sub,col],task_type):

                        results.raw[sub,task + 1][1,1] = mean(rts)

                        results.raw[sub,task + 1][1,3] = mean(rts < 250)
                        results.flags[sub,task + 1][1,1] = mean(rts < 250) <= 0.1
                    else:
                        results.flags[sub,task + 1] = NaN
                        empties[sub,task] = NaN
    
    ## Make final recommendations.
    
    ## Make final recommendations.
    
    for i in np.arange(1,tasks.shape[2-1]+1).reshape(-1):

    # Subject numbers down the side.

    # Task names across the top.

    results.recs.chart[1,np.arange[2,end()+1]] = tasks
    # Overall recs for validating performance:
    chart[:,:,1] = double(cellfun(mean,results.flags(:,np.arange(2,end()+1))) >= tolerance)
    chart[:,:,2] = empties
    chart_final = np.sum(chart, 3-1)
    
    results.recs.chart[np.arange[2,end()+1],np.arange[2,end()+1]] = num2cell(chart_final)
    results.recs.chart[1,end() + 1] = 'Overall'
    overall = double((np.logical_and(np.logical_and(np.logical_and((cell2mat(results.recs.chart(np.arange(2,end()+1),2)) == 1),(cell2mat(results.recs.chart(np.arange(2,end()+1),3)) == 1)),(cell2mat(results.recs.chart(np.arange(2,end()+1),4)) == 1)),(cell2mat(results.recs.chart(np.arange(2,end()+1),5)) == 1))))
    results.recs.chart[np.arange[2,end()+1],end()] = num2cell(overall)
    results.recs.pay = record_id_full_data(cell2mat(results.recs.chart(np.arange(2,end()+1),end())) == 1,1)
    results.recs.remediate = record_id_full_data(cell2mat(results.recs.chart(np.arange(2,end()+1),end())) < 1,1)
    ## Plot
    
    if plot_yesno == 1:
        plt.figure('Color',np.array([1,1,1]))
        map = np.array([[1,0,0],[0,1,0]])
        colormap(map)
        h = imagesc(cell2mat(results.recs.chart(np.arange(2,end()+1),np.arange(2,end()+1))))
        # Set nan values to transparent:
        set(h,'alphadata',not np.isnan(cell2mat(results.recs.chart(np.arange(2,end()+1),np.arange(2,end()+1)))) )
        set(gca,'YTick',np.arange(1,task_data.shape[1-1]+1),'YTickLabel',cellstr(num2str(record_id_full_data)),'XTick',np.arange(1,(results.recs.chart.shape[2-1] - 1)+1),'XTickLabel',results.recs.chart(1,np.arange(2,end()+1)),'XAxisLocation','top')
        plt.ylabel('Record ID')
        xtickangle(30)
        plt.title('Task Performance')
    
    return results
    
    
def custom_cope_phenom_consistency_check(varargin = None): 
    # cope_phenom_consistency_check - Checks for consistency of responses in
# phenomenological data derived from Yale COPE Project.
    
    # IN:
# cell, consisting of data already derived from REDCap records.
    
    # OUT:
# consistency_results - structure with performance data on each of the tasks, including
# measures of randomness response and appropriateness of response given the
# task structure.
    
    ## Get file if needed.
    if len(varargin) == 1:
        cell = varargin[1,1]
    else:
        if len(varargin) == 0:
            file,path = uigetfile('*')
            __,__,cell = xlsread(fullfile(path,file))
    
    ## Config
    
    only_completions = 1
    
    plot_yesno = 0
    
    ## Identify exclusions.
    
    # Exclude if have already been reviewed or included.
# if sum(find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'consistency_quality_check',1))>0
#     already_reviewed = cell2mat(cell(2:end,(find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'consistency_quality_check',0,1))));
#     already_included = cell2mat(cell(2:end,(find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'consistency_quality_check2',0,1))));
    
    #     if only_completions == 1
#         incomplete = isnan(cell2mat(cell(2:end,find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'timestamp4',0,0))));  # timestamp4 generated on completion of Survey2.
#     end
    
    #     all_exclusions = [false; nansum([already_reviewed==1, already_included==1, incomplete],2)>0];  # First row = labels, so should be included in cell_in.
# else
    
    #     if only_completions == 1
#         incomplete = isnan(cell2mat(cell(2:end,find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'timestamp4',0,0))));  # timestamp4 generated on completion of Survey2.
#         all_exclusions = [false; incomplete];
#     else
#         all_exclusions = false(size(cell,1),1);
#     end
# end
    
    # cell_in = cell(~all_exclusions,:);
    
    cell_in = cell
    ## Create variables from all cell columns.
    
    for col in np.arange(1,cell.shape[2-1]+1).reshape(-1):
        eval(np.array([cell_in[1,col],' = cell_in(2:end,col);']))
        try:
            if eval(np.array(['isnumeric(',cell_in[1,col],'{1,1})'])):
                eval(np.array([cell_in[1,col],' = cell2mat(',cell_in[1,col],');']))
        finally:
            pass
    
    ## Test consistency across all measures.
    
    for subject in np.arange(1,record_id.shape[1-1]+1).reshape(-1):
        # Load consistency key.
        if not np.isnan(cb_sash1(subject,1)) :
            scipy.io.loadmat('key.mat')
        else:
            scipy.io.loadmat('key_ah_negative.mat')
        cons_struct = struct
        consistent = np.array([])
        incon_summary = np.array([])
        for test_cond in np.arange(1,key.shape[1-1]+1).reshape(-1):
            for cond_value_num in np.arange(1,key[test_cond,2].shape[1-1]+1).reshape(-1):
                if eval(np.array([key[test_cond,1],'(subject,1)',key[test_cond,2][1,1],num2str(key[test_cond,3](cond_value_num,1))])):
                    inconsistency_count = 0
                    for other_conds in np.arange(1,key[test_cond,4].shape[2-1]+1).reshape(-1):
                        consistent[test_cond,other_conds] = np.sum(eval(np.array([key[test_cond,4][1,other_conds],'(subject,1)',key[test_cond,5][cond_value_num,other_conds],'key{test_cond,6}{cond_value_num,other_conds}'])), 1-1)
                        if consistent[test_cond,other_conds] == 0:
                            inconsistency_count = inconsistency_count + 1
                            if inconsistency_count == 1:
                                # Name of first condition.
                                incon_summary[test_cond,1][1,inconsistency_count] = key[test_cond,1]
                                # Response to first condition.
                                incon_summary[test_cond,1][2,inconsistency_count] = eval(np.array([key[test_cond,1],'(subject,1)']))
                            # Name of test condition.
                            incon_summary[test_cond,2][1,inconsistency_count] = key[test_cond,4][1,other_conds]
                            # Actual response
                            incon_summary[test_cond,2][2,inconsistency_count] = eval(np.array([key[test_cond,4][1,other_conds],'(subject,1)']))
        # Make sure incon summary exists and is not empty.
        if not len(incon_summary)==0 :
            # Clean up summary of what was inconsistent.
            cons_struct.across_scales.incon_summary = incon_summary(not cellfun(isempty,incon_summary(:,1)) ,:)
            # Store data.
            cons_struct.across_scales.test_matrix = consistent
            cons_struct.across_scales.performance = mean(cell2mat(consistent(not cellfun(isempty,consistent) )))
            cons_struct.across_scales.flag = cons_struct.across_scales.performance < 0.75
        else:
            cons_struct.across_scales.flag = 0
        ## Establish performance on cbSASH.
        if not np.isnan(cb_sash1(subject,1)) :
            # Malingering.
            cons_struct.cbsash.malingering_responses = np.array([[cb_sash142(subject,1)],[cb_sash9(subject,1)],[cb_sash10(subject,1)],[cb_sash19(subject,1)],[cb_sash20(subject,1)],[cb_sash29(subject,1)],[cb_sash35(subject,1)],[cb_sash39(subject,1)],[cb_sash40(subject,1)],[cb_sash66(subject,1)],[cb_sash68(subject,1)],[cb_sash74(subject,1)],[cb_sash76(subject,1)],[cb_sash80(subject,1)],[cb_sash81(subject,1)],[cb_sash82(subject,1)],[cb_sash83(subject,1)],[cb_sash98(subject,1)],[cb_sash103(subject,1)],[cb_sash104(subject,1)],[cb_sash108(subject,1)],[cb_sash111(subject,1)],[cb_sash112(subject,1)],[cb_sash120(subject,1)],[cb_sash127(subject,1)],[cb_sash130(subject,1)],[cb_sash154(subject,1)],[cb_sash34(subject,1)],[cb_sash51(subject,1)],[cb_sash53(subject,1)]]) == 1
            cons_struct.cbsash.malingering_flag = np.sum(cons_struct.cbsash.malingering_responses, 1-1) > 7
            cons_struct.cbsash.malingering_sum = np.sum(cons_struct.cbsash.malingering_responses, 1-1)
            cons_struct.cbsash.malingering_mean = mean(cons_struct.cbsash.malingering_responses,1)
            # Items that should be consistent.
            cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses = np.array([[cb_sash2(subject,1),cb_sash156(subject,1)],[cb_sash11(subject,1),cb_sash139(subject,1)],[cb_sash12(subject,1),cb_sash140(subject,1)],[cb_sash15(subject,1),cb_sash121(subject,1)],[cb_sash16(subject,1),cb_sash116(subject,1)],[cb_sash3(subject,1),cb_sash77(subject,1)],[cb_sash95(subject,1),cb_sash144(subject,1)],[cb_sash38(subject,1),cb_sash132(subject,1)],[cb_sash101(subject,1),cb_sash146(subject,1)],[cb_sash49(subject,1),cb_sash138(subject,1)],[cb_sash5(subject,1),cb_sash131(subject,1)],[cb_sash13(subject,1),cb_sash65(subject,1)],[cb_sash56(subject,1),cb_sash129(subject,1)],[cb_sash96(subject,1),cb_sash150(subject,1)]])
            cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses_correct = cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses(:,1) == cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses(:,2)
            cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses_correct_sum = np.sum(cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses_correct, 1-1)
            cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses_correct_mean = mean(cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses_correct,1)
            cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses_correct_flag = cons_struct.cbsash.consistent_responses_correct_mean < 0.7
            # Items that should be inconsistent.
            cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses = np.array([[cb_sash18(subject,1),cb_sash87(subject,1)],[cb_sash121(subject,1),cb_sash79(subject,1)],[cb_sash44(subject,1),cb_sash134(subject,1)],[cb_sash141(subject,1),cb_sash45(subject,1)],[cb_sash48(subject,1),cb_sash142(subject,1)],[cb_sash78(subject,1),cb_sash143(subject,1)],[cb_sash37(subject,1),cb_sash136(subject,1)],[cb_sash60(subject,1),cb_sash123(subject,1)],[cb_sash99(subject,1),cb_sash151(subject,1)],[cb_sash128(subject,1),cb_sash14(subject,1)],[cb_sash8(subject,1),cb_sash157(subject,1)],[cb_sash59(subject,1),cb_sash178(subject,1)],[cb_sash148(subject,1),cb_sash43(subject,1)],[cb_sash69(subject,1),cb_sash133(subject,1)]])
            cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses_correct = cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses(:,1) != cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses(:,2)
            cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses_correct_sum = np.sum(cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses_correct, 1-1)
            cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses_correct_mean = mean(cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses_correct,1)
            cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses_correct_flag = cons_struct.cbsash.inconsistent_responses_correct_mean < 0.7
        ## Establish performance on MFAST.
        # Reported vs observed.
        try:
            cons_struct.mfast.reported_vs_observed_responses = np.array([[mfast1(subject,1),mfast1a(subject,1)],[mfast7(subject,1),mfast7b(subject,1)],[mfast11(subject,1),mfast11b(subject,1)]])
            cons_struct.mfast.reported_vs_observed_incorrect = cons_struct.mfast.reported_vs_observed_responses(:,1) != cons_struct.mfast.reported_vs_observed_responses(:,2)
        finally:
            pass
        cons_struct.mfast.reported_vs_observed_flag = np.sum(cons_struct.mfast.reported_vs_observed_incorrect, 1-1) >= 1
        # Extreme Symptoms.
        cons_struct.mfast.extreme_symptoms = np.array([[mfast2(subject,1)],[mfast5(subject,1)],[mfast8(subject,1)],[mfast10(subject,1)],[mfast13(subject,1)],[mfast15(subject,1)],[mfast19(subject,1)]])
        cons_struct.mfast.extreme_symptoms_endorsed = cons_struct.mfast.extreme_symptoms > 0
        cons_struct.mfast.extreme_symptoms_flag = np.sum(cons_struct.mfast.extreme_symptoms_endorsed, 1-1) >= 2
        # Rare Combinations
        cons_struct.mfast.rare_combinations = np.array([[mfast3(subject,1)],[mfast12(subject,1)],[mfast16(subject,1)],[mfast17(subject,1)],[mfast18(subject,1)],[mfast22(subject,1)],[mfast24(subject,1)]])
        cons_struct.mfast.rare_combinations_endorsed = cons_struct.mfast.rare_combinations > 0
        cons_struct.mfast.rare_combinations_flag = np.sum(cons_struct.mfast.rare_combinations_endorsed, 1-1) >= 2
        # Unusual symptom course
        cons_struct.mfast.unusual_symptom_course = np.array([[mfast4(subject,1)],[mfast6(subject,1)],[mfast9(subject,1)],[mfast20(subject,1)],[mfast21(subject,1)]])
        cons_struct.mfast.unusual_symptom_course_endorsed = cons_struct.mfast.unusual_symptom_course > 0
        cons_struct.mfast.unusual_symptom_course_flag = np.sum(cons_struct.mfast.unusual_symptom_course_endorsed, 1-1) >= 2
        # Total scores.
        cons_struct.mfast.total_score = np.sum(np.array([[cons_struct.mfast.reported_vs_observed_incorrect],[cons_struct.mfast.extreme_symptoms_endorsed],[cons_struct.mfast.rare_combinations_endorsed],[cons_struct.mfast.unusual_symptom_course_endorsed]]), 1-1)
        cons_struct.mfast.clin_flag = cons_struct.mfast.total_score > 10
        cons_struct.mfast.nonclin_flag = cons_struct.mfast.total_score > 6
        ## Store data.
        results[subject,1] = record_id(subject,1)
        results[subject,2] = cons_struct
    
    ## Plot data.
    
    if plot_yesno == 1:
        # Flags:
        flags = np.array(['Across Scales Poor Performance Flag','MFAST Reported vs Observed Flag','MFAST Extreme Symptoms Flag','MFAST Rare Combinations Flag','MFAST Unusual Course Flag','MFAST Clin Flag','MFAST Non-Clin Flag','cbSASH Malingering Flag','cbSASH Consistent Items Flag','cbSASH Inconsistent Items Flag'])
        for subject in np.arange(1,record_id.shape[1-1]+1).reshape(-1):
            flag_values[subject,np.arange[1,7+1]] = double(np.array([results[subject,2].across_scales.flag,results[subject,2].mfast.reported_vs_observed_flag,results[subject,2].mfast.extreme_symptoms_flag,results[subject,2].mfast.rare_combinations_flag,results[subject,2].mfast.unusual_symptom_course_flag,results[subject,2].mfast.clin_flag,results[subject,2].mfast.nonclin_flag]))
            if isfield(results[subject,2],'cbsash'):
                flag_values[subject,np.arange[8,10+1]] = double(np.array([results[subject,2].cbsash.malingering_flag,results[subject,2].cbsash.consistent_responses_correct_flag,results[subject,2].cbsash.inconsistent_responses_correct_flag]))
            else:
                flag_values[subject,np.arange[8,10+1]] = NaN
        plt.figure('Color',np.array([1,1,1]))
        map = np.array([np.transpose((np.arange(0,1+0.01,0.01))),np.transpose((np.arange(1,0+- 0.01,- 0.01))),np.zeros((101,1))])
        colormap(map)
        h = imagesc(flag_values)
        # Set nan values to transparent:
        set(h,'alphadata',not np.isnan(flag_values) )
        #     # Make the background black:
#     set(gca,'color','black')
        set(gca,'YTick',np.arange(1,record_id.shape[1-1]+1),'YTickLabel',cellstr(num2str(record_id)),'XTick',np.arange(1,flags.shape[2-1]+1),'XTickLabel',flags,'XAxisLocation','top')
        plt.ylabel('Record ID')
        xtickangle(30)
        plt.title('Phenomenological Performance')
    
    return results
    
    
def ip_repeat_check(cell = None): 
    qualifying_tasks = np.logical_and(find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'qualifying',1),not find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'complete',1) )
    complete_qualifying = np.sum(not cellfun(isnumeric,cell(np.arange(2,end()+1),qualifying_tasks)) , 2-1) > 0
    complete_qualifying_data = cell(np.array([[False],[complete_qualifying]]),qualifying_tasks)
    record_id = cell2mat(cell(np.array([[False],[complete_qualifying]]),find_in_cellstr(cell(1,:),'record_id',0,1)))
    for record in np.arange(1,record_id.shape[1-1]+1).reshape(-1):
        # Convert to cellstr.
        complete_qualifying_data[cellfun[isnumeric,complete_qualifying_data]] = np.array([''])
        # Find relevant data.
        real_data = find_in_cellstr(complete_qualifying_data(record,:),'H4s')
        data[record,1] = redcap2struct(real_data[1,1])
        if isfield(data[record,1],'ip'):
            ip[record,1] = data[record,1].ip
        else:
            symbols = np.array([np.arange('a','z'+1),np.arange('A','Z'+1),np.arange('0','9'+1)])
            MAX_ST_LENGTH = 50
            stLength = randi(MAX_ST_LENGTH)
            nums = randi(np.asarray(symbols).size,np.array([1,stLength]))
            st = symbols(nums)
            ip[record,1] = st
    
    __,i,__ = unique(ip,'first')
    results = record_id(not_(ismember(np.arange(1,np.asarray(ip).size+1),i)),1)
    return results
